evidence.dc:description:
Points reduced since consanguineous; 
Variant is located in exon 4 of 64 and is therefore expected to undergo nonsense mediated decay. Absent from gnomAD.  
Affected brother (deceased at 10 mo - also 9 mo at last exam [patient 19]) and two cousins ([patients 21 and 22] - WES on sib and one cousin); another older sib who is deceased (spasticity and developmental delay) - no genotype information; cannot score for segregation.

Default points since non-consanguineous; Compound heterozygous status confirmed - each parent had one of the variants; 
Variants are located in exons 14 and 26 of 64, respectively and are therefore expected to undergo nonsense mediated decay.  Both are absent from gnomAD.

Another homozygous missense variant (NARS2 NM_024678.5:c.291G>T (p.Gln97His)) was also detected which is absent from gnomAD; no literature on variant; in silico predicted this other variant to be benign. ClinGen limited GDA with Leigh syndrome [Dec 2019] so was not investigated further.

Points reduced since consanguineous and use of a cryptic splice site preserves the reading frame; 
Variant is located in intron 53 of 63.
All predictors in Varsome + SpliceAI suggest it is deleterious; 
Application of Abou Tayoun et al. (2018) criteria for application of PVS1 show that it can be applied at moderate; 
Two entries in ClinVar by laboratories (LP and P).
Absent from gnomAD.
